    assert row["altman_z"] == 3.4
    assert row["analyst_sent"] == 4.2  # rec_mark 0.6 -> 4.2
    assert result.universe == "SP500"


def test_tv_registered():
    names = {p["name"] for p in list_providers()}
    assert "tradingview" in names
5. SOP — docs/algorithms/data_providers.md (recommended addition)
Brief note that TradingView is unofficial and gated behind a single warning string returned in ProviderResult.warnings. Important to flag in the explainability narrative.

6. Run after applying
cd /c/Users/User/trio-web
source .venv/Scripts/activate
pip install -e packages/data_providers     # pick up the new module
cd apps/api && pytest -q                    # should be 32 passed
cd ../web && ./node_modules/.bin/next build # confirm LiveUniverseCard resolves
What this gets you
TradingView is now the 4th provider, hitting scanner.tradingview.com/{america|malaysia}/scan — gives you full BOS field coverage (incl. ALT.Z) for both US and KLSE in one provider, which neither yfinance (US-only) nor i3investor (target+sentiment only) can match.
The web UI's LiveUniverseCard now exists, so page.tsx (already updated to import it) will build.
Caveat surfaced to the user: every TradingView response carries the warning "unofficial scanner endpoint — schema may change without notice" — flows straight into the existing yellow-banner footer of ResultsTable.
If TradingView's column IDs (ALT.Z, recommendation_mark, etc.) drift, only tradingview_provider.py needs to change — the scoring engine and contracts stay stable.

